  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nFor the filter in Don't Starve Together, see Weapons Filter and Armor Filter.\nTab Icon\n“En garde!”\n–Webber\nFight items and structures can be obtained from Crafting, in the Fight tab with the Crossed Swords icon on the left-hand side.\nSee all the Weapons in the game.\nSee all the Armors in the game.\nDownloadable Content[edit | edit source]\nIn the Reign of Giants DLC, the player can craft Weather Pains, Scalemails, Morning Stars, and while playing as Wigfrid, Battle Spears, and Battle Helms in the Fight Tab.\nIn the Shipwrecked DLC, Poison Spears, Seashell Suits, Limestone Suits, Cactus Armors, Horned Helmets, Poison Darts, Coconades, Spear Guns, and Cutlass Supremes were added to the Fight Tab.\nThe Hamlet DLC introduces Halberds, Cork Bats, Weevole Mantles, Mant Masks, Mant Suits, Fancy Helmets, Tin Suits and Blunderbusses.\nCraftable Items and Structures[edit | edit source]\nThe following items and structures can be crafted in the Fight Tab:\nSpear\nHam Bat\nGrass Suit\nLog Suit\nMarble Suit\nFootball Helmet\nSleep Dart\nFire Dart\nBlow Dart\nBoomerang\nBee Mine\nTooth Trap\nWeather Pain\nScalemail\nMorning Star\nBattle Spear\nBattle Helm\nPoison Spear\nSeashell Suit\nLimestone Suit\nCactus Armor\nHorned Helmet\nPoison Dart\nCoconade\nSpear Gun\nCutlass Supreme\nHalberd\nCork Bat\nWeevole Mantle\nMant Mask\nMant Suit\nFancy Helmet\nTin Suit\nBlunderbuss\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nThe Fight Tab icon is available for use on Steam as a chat emoticon.\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Crafting Tabs\nRegular\nTools\nLight\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\n(Nautical )\n(Treasure Hunting )\nCharacter-Specific\nBooks\nTinkering\n(Green Thumb )\nNon-prototypable\nAncient\nVolcanic\n(Renovate\nCity Planning )",
